04/21/2022,748.2307(9) - Individual Standards Evaluated,Individual Standards Evaluated,No,06/24/2022,06/15/2022,Individual Standards Evaluated,Medium High,Yes,Staff has been cursing towards children in an inappropriate manner heard by staff and residents. ,"Boysville has completed the compliance plan in reference to the findings in Investigation #2876843 that 
alleged that children in care were threatened.
 Standard 748.2307 (9) Other Prohibited Punishments  subjecting a child to abusive or profane 
language
Specifics: Staff has been cursing towards children in an inappropriate manner heard by staff 
and residents.
Technical Assistance Given: Staff should not use inappropriate language to threaten children. 
The purpose of this rule is to prevent harm to children due to the use of behavior management 
techniques that inflict physical or emotional pain or discomfort. These prohibited methods of 
punishment are considered physically, psychologically and/or emotionally abusive.
Corrective Action Plan: Staff involved in the incident has retaken the EBI Satori Alternatives to 
Managing Aggression (SAMA) training on 6/1/2022. Staff has also received written feedback 
from their supervisor and will be monitored closely with weekly check ins. Staff will also not 
work alone with children to ensure all compliance for policies/procedures"
